    Example object and IDs for testing

    examples.Rd

    Make some example objects for testing.

    exampleObject()

exampleID()

    Value

    For exampleObject, a DFrame is returned with annotation set by annotateObject.

    For exampleID, a string is returned containing an example ID.

    Author

    Aaron Lun

    Examples

    exampleObject()
#> DataFrame with 10 rows and 4 columns
#>            X           Y        Z                  AA
#>    <integer> <character> <factor>         <DataFrame>
#> 1          1           A        a 0.5666612:-0.466668
#> 2          2           B        b 0.0924448: 0.391301
#> 3          3           C        c 0.8814183: 1.684336
#> 4          4           D        d 0.7570433:-0.967521
#> 5          5           E        e 0.4308979: 0.943331
#> 6          6           F        f 0.3992868: 0.353795
#> 7          7           G        g 0.2612118:-0.225758
#> 8          8           H        h 0.4906047:-0.310337
#> 9          9           I        i 0.1700199:-3.694818
#> 10        10           J        j 0.8175136: 0.815265
exampleID()
#> [1] "test:my_first_df@v1"
